== Chips ==

Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Remove the @21 Day Aged British Rump Steaks{2} from your fridge to allow them to come up to room temperature.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g}(chopped lengthways into 1cm slices, then into 1cm wide chips), no need to peel.

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%mins}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, remove the @SlooOW Stone Oven White Baguette{1} from the packaging and pop onto a baking tray. Bake on the middle shelf until toasted and golden, ~{10-12%mins}. Once baked, allow to cool.

== Caramelised Onions ==

While everything bakes, halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} and a knob of @?butter{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat.

Once hot, add the onion, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and fry, stirring occasionally, until golden and softened, ~{8-10%mins}.

Add the @sugar{1/2%tsp} and cook until caramelised, ~{1-2%mins} more.

While the onion cooks, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}.

Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}.

When the onions are cooked, transfer to a small #bowl{}. Stir in the @fig jam{40%g} and cover with a #lid{} to keep warm.

== Red Wine Jus ==

Next, pour the @water{200%ml} into a small #saucepan{} and bring to the boil on high heat.

Stir in the @red wine jus paste{22%g}, then reduce the heat to medium-high.

> TIP: If your red wine jus paste has hardened, put the sachet in a bowl of hot water for ~{1%min} to loosen.

Allow the sauce to bubble and thicken, stirring regularly, ~{8-9%mins}. Once thickened, remove from the heat, cover and set aside.

== Steaks and Baguette ==

Wipe out the (now empty) frying pan, then return to a high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}. Season the steaks with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> TIP: Rump steaks naturally vary in shape, so adjust the following timings depending on how you like yours cooked.

Once very hot, lay the steaks into the pan and fry until browned and medium-rare, about ~{5%mins}. Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Cook each side for ~{1%minute} more if you like it more well done.

Once the steaks are cooked, transfer to a #board{}, cover with #foil{} and allow to rest for a couple of mins.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. The steak is safe to eat when browned on the outside.

== Assembly and Salad ==

While the steaks cook, slice the baguette in half lengthways.

Spread the caramelised onions over the base and sprinkle the Cheddar over the lid. Return the baguette to the middle shelf of the oven until the cheese has melted, ~{3-5%mins}.

Once melted, remove the baguette from the oven. Top with the sliced steak and spoon over 2 tbsp of the red wine jus, then sandwich shut and slice in half widthways.

Just before everything's ready, in a large bowl, toss the @wild rocket{40%g} and tomatoes with the @balsamic glaze{12%ml}.

Share your steak sandwiches between your plates.

Reheat the remaining red wine jus if needed, then transfer to small #bowls{} and serve alongside for dipping.

Serve the chips and salad alongside. Enjoy!